    <div><p><a title="Companies > Nippon Ichi Software [1,099 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/nippon-ichi-software">Nippon Ichi Software</a> president Tetsuhisa Seko has passed away at the age of 54, the company <a href="https://nippon1.co.jp/news/pdf/2025/20250124_01.pdf" target="_blank">announced</a>. <span id="more-940324"></span></p><p>Seko joined Nippon Ichi Software in March 2002 after working at <a title="Companies > SNK Corporation [408 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/snk">SNK</a> and Toshin, and after moving through various <a title="Genres > Management [27 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/management">management</a> positions, was appointed president and representative director of Nippon Ichi Software in July 2023.</p><p>According to <a href="https://www.jiji.com/jc/article?k=2025012400841&amp;g=obt" target="_blank">Jiji</a>, Seko passed away in the hospital. A funeral will be held at Memoire Kakamigahara on January 29 at 11:00 JST.</p></div>

        
    
